<subSubSection id="BC99B743135173A1F2CC692683EDEC73" pageId="0" pageNumber="153" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="71CB0A7CBBF30B4B2C2F37FCF70412AC" pageId="0" pageNumber="153">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B33A08A0BD8B7D09C8A929448B6E5C8D" pageId="0" pageNumber="153">
<taxonomicName id="E396BF0C90A40709D6C5C9E46C9E1356" baseAuthorityName="Yaginuma" baseAuthorityYear="1952" class="Arachnida" family="Theridiidae" genus="Meotipa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Meotipa argyrodiformis" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="153" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="argyrodiformis">
<emphasis id="112C5D2CDF9D54DC1BD1DBAE1EBFC0FB" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="153">Meotipa argyrodiformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="2755E477A8514917B97636C9E01C21E5" genus="M." lsidName="M. pulcherrima" pageId="0" pageNumber="153" rank="species" species="pulcherrima">
<emphasis id="458C7BB620634F7C8BEF3C2E6014DCA9" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="153">M. pulcherrima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="1ED8BE0DA1CE843BA7BEDD7FEAD55CB7" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Meotipa pulcherrima (Mello-Leitao, 1917) A-C female habitus (flattened black spines on the abdomen and legs were broken off during photography) (A dorsal B prolateral C ventral). D-H epigynum (D ventral, on the body, and the arrow points to tongue-shaped apophysis E, F in alcohol E ventral F dorsal G, H in gum arabic G ventral H dorsal). Scale bars: 1 mm (A-C); 0.1 mm (D-H). Abbreviations: CD = copulatory duct, FD = fertilization duct, S = spermathecae." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1082.75400.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/636293" pageId="0" pageNumber="153">2A-H</figureCitation>
) in: having the abdomen pointed to a tubercle posteriorly (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="D2E6A7362A1502683D6A4AB43CCA01F9" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Meotipa argyrodiformis (Yaginuma, 1952) A-C female habitus (some flattened black spines on the abdomen and legs were broken off during photography) (A dorsal B prolateral C ventral). D-H epigynum (D ventral, on the body E, F in alcohol E ventral F dorsal G, H in gum arabic G ventral H dorsal). Scale bars: 1 mm (A-C); 0.1 mm (D-H). Abbreviations: CD = copulatory duct, FD = fertilization duct, S = spermathecae." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1082.75400.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/636292" pageId="0" pageNumber="153">1B</figureCitation>
), lacking obvious copulatory openings, and having a spoon-shaped conductor in the male palp. However, it can be distinguished from the latter by the following combination of characters: (1) the abdomen extends beyond spinnerets ~ 3/4 of total abdomen length in 
<taxonomicName id="1B90674CB8C400EB87DE1566122ADAB5" genus="M." lsidName="M. argyrodiformis" pageId="0" pageNumber="153" rank="species" species="argyrodiformis">
<emphasis id="ABE265375F6AB0735843D14BE8B016C9" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="153">M. argyrodiformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="5FCFCEFFC32895140D3F76CE02BE9B6E" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Meotipa argyrodiformis (Yaginuma, 1952) A-C female habitus (some flattened black spines on the abdomen and legs were broken off during photography) (A dorsal B prolateral C ventral). D-H epigynum (D ventral, on the body E, F in alcohol E ventral F dorsal G, H in gum arabic G ventral H dorsal). Scale bars: 1 mm (A-C); 0.1 mm (D-H). Abbreviations: CD = copulatory duct, FD = fertilization duct, S = spermathecae." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1082.75400.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/636292" pageId="0" pageNumber="153">1A</figureCitation>
), but less than half in 
<taxonomicName id="2DA3B664528368D8E54D12E624460382" genus="M." lsidName="M. pulcherrima" pageId="0" pageNumber="153" rank="species" species="pulcherrima">
<emphasis id="258D78DF77F3709CDE841BE5E31E8AE2" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="153">M. pulcherrima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="B5368B5D911652B303749DDFFC7A5456" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Meotipa pulcherrima (Mello-Leitao, 1917) A-C female habitus (flattened black spines on the abdomen and legs were broken off during photography) (A dorsal B prolateral C ventral). D-H epigynum (D ventral, on the body, and the arrow points to tongue-shaped apophysis E, F in alcohol E ventral F dorsal G, H in gum arabic G ventral H dorsal). Scale bars: 1 mm (A-C); 0.1 mm (D-H). Abbreviations: CD = copulatory duct, FD = fertilization duct, S = spermathecae." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1082.75400.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/636293" pageId="0" pageNumber="153">2A</figureCitation>
); (2) the epigynum does not have a tongue-shaped apophysis posteriorly and medially in 
<taxonomicName id="B813B77F45A4AEBE1433ED23D150945D" genus="M." lsidName="M. argyrodiformis" pageId="0" pageNumber="153" rank="species" species="argyrodiformis">
<emphasis id="3827023F8C1AB0B6FDCE125DE5130712" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="153">M. argyrodiformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="39B3261CD32788D844D2362C9AF90D0A" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Meotipa argyrodiformis (Yaginuma, 1952) A-C female habitus (some flattened black spines on the abdomen and legs were broken off during photography) (A dorsal B prolateral C ventral). D-H epigynum (D ventral, on the body E, F in alcohol E ventral F dorsal G, H in gum arabic G ventral H dorsal). Scale bars: 1 mm (A-C); 0.1 mm (D-H). Abbreviations: CD = copulatory duct, FD = fertilization duct, S = spermathecae." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1082.75400.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/636292" pageId="0" pageNumber="153">1D</figureCitation>
), but has in 
<taxonomicName id="8B9E083E33D021D0684C49C1A1BA9E7B" genus="M." lsidName="M. pulcherrima" pageId="0" pageNumber="153" rank="species" species="pulcherrima">
